hem did you see hit 60 and retire / twink a melee alt ?<br><br>Sol is better in that there is MUCH more a single group can do.  Mages can bring extra damage to a 6 person group still just fine, with their nice pets, damage shield and nukes.<br><br>many of the mobs in SoL seem almost &quot; melee resistant&quot; in that they have High ac so the melee hit for less than normal, but they nuke just fine.<br><br>the problem comes if you belong to a guild whose goal is to raid ubermobs every day.  In such an atmosphere, you have a chance to aquire loot, but dont get a chance to flexx the muscle of your class ( for many classes ).<br><br>course this is all personal opinion, but i find very very few &quot; support&quot; type classes that are happy to raid every day.  The classes that normally enjoy it :<br><br>War<br>Rog<br>Clr<br>wiz<br><br>Other melee tend to enjoy it sometimes, because they get to stand up front and go toe to toe with some nasty mean son of a bitch mob.<br><br>Clerics role doesnt change, so there is no shock at what they are doing on ubermob encounters.<br><br>Necros, Mages, Enchanters.. their roles change 180 degrees, and if you look around you will find these classes either drop like flies if they raid constantly, or, make alts so they dont have to play these classes on raids all the time.<br><br>The only solution i can see is to do more 1-2 group things and less 30 person raids.  You might re capture what you found fun about EQ in the first place.<br><br> <p><a href="http://www.mithrilweb.com//"target="web"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/images/sigs/llosig.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugamrok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#0