ticons2/4.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Sandra Storm <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.animemtv.prohosting.com/emoticons6/12.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>60 Arch Mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ucicelygoldenfair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cicely goldenfair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lanys Cheerleader</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/16/02 9:39:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: da mage</span><hr size=1> funny.  verant should stop giving us stupid summoning spells?  last time i checked, a magician's power was the ability to summon stuff...<br><br>while some of the spells are kinda silly and not used much, magicians are the masters of summoning.  and to that extent, verant has given us all these summon spells so that we can continue to be the only class with the ability to summon as much stuff as we can.<br><br>i don't think gamrok really wants new spells.  i think he just wants the ability to land a spell on some of the uber mobs in the game, the ability for his pet to be beneficial against some of the uber mobs in the game, and for everyone to recognize magicians as more than just mod rod 2....<br> <p>Cicely Goldenfair <BR>Lanys Cheerleader <BR>Lvl 60 Arch Mage <BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=10393">Magelo Profile</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugamrok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>p0\/\/3r-p0sT3r!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/16/02 1:25:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: da mage</span><hr size=1> It doesn't have to necessarily be a spell, AA points that give the ability for more than one pet would be one thing that would at least help my burnout, since I would benefit more from exping.<br><br>Aside from an overhaul of how pets work (damage-wise), I think spells such as Summon Primal (Pet only like muzzle, dropped in ST), <Instert Good Name> a spell that would add +50% damage, hps, resists or whatever to our pet that is dropped off a high level mob.  <br><br>While melee get their amazing 15/18's etc. dropping off Some SoL and SoV mobs, mages continue to just get more mana, hit points and resists (Flowing thought has become a common effect as well, but not near as common as haste).  So, melee increase their damage, hit points, resists and even mana for hybrids substantially while we settle for just stat increases with nothing good to use that extra mana on other than summoning mod rods.  <br><br>Although mod rods do help a lot, I'll admit that, they are not fun, and even Clerics who "just heal" can buff, Shamans who "just slow" buff as well, rangers buff, heal, melee and do bow damage.  All I'm asking for is the 'slow' or 'heal' of the mage class to accompany our mod rod dispenser status.  Also, I know that we have damage shields, but I was thinking more along the lines of something that is used as often as heals and slows (God I'm gonna get a lot of arguments for that!).<br><br>(I know I'm jumping all over the place and not making much sense, but I'm in a rush =p )<br><br>No matter how good the pathing was, I would very rarely summon a pet on a high end raid vs. a single mob or for the clearing.  Although the pet would help against mobs, the melee damage of the epic pet when not tanking is approximately 40dps I think, which is absolutely terrible.  The risk of it breaking even one mez, or aggroing one mob is not worth the risk of that added damage, in my opinion.  <br><br>Now, I know that multiple pets isn't exactly something that falls into what I'm talking about, but this would be our parallel skill to Dire Charm, something that would allow us to solo/group much better with the added damage.  Summon primal also benefits only ourselves, but with that and maybe some sort of spell that gives added damage, immunities, AC and hit points to our pets then perhaps they just might be worth summoning on a high level raid.<br><br>Some other spells that might help, Buffs that deal with the elements, but not actual illusions... For example; Fire buffy thing could increase attack with a small DS, water buff could increase mana and hit point regeneration, earth could increase hit points and resists, air could give see invis and maybe haste or AC.<br><br>I'm not really sure what the point of this post was, and I'm sorry if it's hard to understand with all the grammar mistakes and topic jumping..<br><br>Edit:  Just read an idea over on the Mage Compendium.. Having weapons with bane damage and procs would be great, and would fit into the masters of summoning role. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugamrok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gamrok</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/16/02 1:29:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usandrastorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SandraStorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t d00d!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/16/02 5:12:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummagician.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: da mage</span><hr size=1> What I ment by stupid 